ACT:
 Limitation Act, 1963--First Schedule--Articles 58 and 113--'When the right to sue or cause of action first ac- crues'--Interpretation of--Held to be not from the date of original adverse order but from the date when the order on the statutory appeal is made or six months from the date of preferring statutory appeal--Statutory appeals to be dis- posed of expeditiously--Ordinarily a period of three to six months to be the outer limit.
 
